ğŸ”¹ STEP 1: Update your system

Open a terminal and run:

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

ğŸ”¹ STEP 2: Set up locale (important for ROS)
sudo apt install locales
sudo locale-gen en_US en_US.UTF-8
sudo update-locale LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8 LANG=en_US.UTF-8
export LANG=en_US.UTF-8

ğŸ”¹ STEP 3: Add ROS 2 repository
sudo apt install software-properties-common
sudo add-apt-repository universe

Add the ROS key:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install curl -y
sudo curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ros/rosdistro/master/ros.key \
  -o /usr/share/keyrings/ros-archive-keyring.gpg

ğŸ”¹ STEP 4: Install ROS 2 Humble (Recommended)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ros-humble-desktop -y


â³ This may take a few minutes.

ğŸ”¹ STEP 5: Source ROS automatically

Add this line to your .bashrc:

echo "source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash" >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc

ğŸ”¹ STEP 6: Install build tools
sudo apt install python3-colcon-common-extensions -y

ğŸ”¹ STEP 7: Test ROS 2 installation ğŸ‰

Open two terminals.

Terminal 1:
ros2 run demo_nodes_cpp talker

Terminal 2:
ros2 run demo_nodes_py listener

What is a Node?

A node is a program that does one job.

Example:

talker â†’ sends messages

listener â†’ receives messages

What is a Topic?

A topic is a communication channel between nodes.

ğŸ”¹ Explore running nodes

Open a new terminal:

ros2 node list

You should see:

/talker
/listener

ğŸ”¹ Listen to a topic
ros2 topic echo /chatter


Youâ€™ll see messages like:

data: "Hello World: 42"

